creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: roundel: female figure with windblown dress, balancing on one leg on a winged ball, with both arms raised upward; behind her is a rugged valley with a few buildings including a house, churches, and castles
inscription:
Signature, Date, Inscription

inscribed in plate at top: [ERRAT. PER. TRIFTDVM. FORTVNA. VOLVBILIS. ORBEM. / OMNIPOTENTI. TAMEN. REGITVR. ILLA. MANV.]
provenance: John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
signed: monogram and date in plate, at top: [1540 AS]
title: Fortune
